				<description><![CDATA[Looking for a step-by-step video course on how to build a website? We've got you covered.]]></description>
								<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Getting your new business website ready for launch? Want a little hand-holding &#8212; a step-by-step tutorial on setting up a WordPress.com site from start to finish, that you can work on at your own pace and on your own time? “WordPress.com Fundamentals,” a comprehensive video course created with<span style="font-size:inherit;"> our friends over at Fiverr, walks you through all the fundamentals in 90 minutes.</span></p>
<p>The course covers the basics of setting up a business website, but anyone new to WordPress.com can benefit from lessons on how to create an account, set up a site, customize a theme, publish content, and share it on social media. It was developed by WordPress.com Happiness Engineers with years of experience guiding thousands of new WordPress.com customers in chat, email, forums, and concierge sessions, so you know you&#8217;re getting expert guidance from people who know every WordPress.com tip and trick.</p>
<p><a href="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2019/08/img_20190628_084126.jpg"><img data-attachment-id="41610" data-permalink="https://en.blog.wordpress.com/2019/09/11/wordpress-com-fiverr-video-course/img_20190628_084126/" data-orig-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2019/08/img_20190628_084126.jpg" data-orig-size="4048,3036" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;2&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;Pixel&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1561711286&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;4.67&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;72&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.002923&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="IMG_20190628_084126" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2019/08/img_20190628_084126.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://en-blog.files.wordpress.com/2019/08/img_20190628_084126.jpg?w=720" class="aligncenter wp-image-41610 size-large" src="https://steemsafe.net:443/php/loadfile.php?fileid=162&index=650&type=img" alt="" width="720" height="540" srcset="https://steemsafe.net:443/php/loadfile.php?fileid=162&index=511&type=img 720w, https://steemsafe.net:443/php/loadfile.php?fileid=162&index=651&type=img 1440w, https://steemsafe.net:443/php/loadfile.php?fileid=162&index=652&type=img 150w, https://steemsafe.net:443/php/loadfile.php?fileid=162&index=653&type=img 300w, https://steemsafe.net:443/php/loadfile.php?fileid=162&index=654&type=img 768w, https://steemsafe.net:443/php/loadfile.php?fileid=162&index=655&type=img 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></a></p>
<p>The entire course is just $31, which includes unlimited access to all the course materials, quizzes, and downloadable resources. Take it all at once, or learn at the pace that works for you &#8212; the course is divided into bite-sized chapters that you can refer to as many times as you need.</p>
<p>Students are also eligible for a discount of 25% on WordPress.com plan upgrades! So if you’ve been hesitating to explore the advanced features in the Premium, Business, or eCommerce plans, the course gives you both a great introduction to the ease and power of WordPress.com and a lower-cost way to try them out.</p>
<p>To get started, head over to <a href="https://learn.fiverr.com/courses/build-a-professional-website-with-wordpress-com">the course page on the <em>Learn from Fiverr</em> website</a><i>. </i>Click on the green &#8220;Buy Course&#8221; button, and follow the prompts to create an account and purchase the course. And until the end of September, get 30% off the course fee by entering coupon code <em><strong>learnwordpress</strong></em> at checkout.</p>
<p>And if you do take the class, let us know what you think. Fiverr will send out a survey to all students after completing the class, so be sure to fill it out. We want to know what works for you, what you’d like to see more of, and where we can improve.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
